description:
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting for experienced band 6 nurses with a post graduate qualification in critical care to join our world class Adult Critical Care Unit at the Royal London Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are extremely proud to have been rated as ‘outstanding’ for caring by the Care Quality Commission in 2016 and this year Barts Hero Award Winners:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;@Team ACCU were:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Winner of: ‘Fund raising Team’ of the Year raising donations by competing in the Tough Mudder Challenge and from fund raising with patients families.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Highly recommended for Engaging with their patients&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the UK’s largest trauma centre we lead the trauma network for North East London and Essex. We are a leading specialist centre with an international reputation for caring for some of the most sick and seriously injured patients in London and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care for a diverse range of specialties including trauma, neurosciences, acute general medical, surgical, obstetric and hyper-acute stroke, giving the opportunity for varied learning and clinical exposure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Professional development is very important to us and we offer you the opportunity to undertake the neurosciences critical care course/ILS/ALS, we are supporting a number of staff on their degree/masters pathways and we are currently collaborating with City University to run an accredited Trauma Course in house.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our Adult Critical Care commitment to enhance the working lives of our staff, we offer flexible working arrangements, childcare vouchers, family-friendly policies and staff benefits including an excellent pension scheme. We are committed to providing a culture of continuous learning, which actively supports the professional and personal development of our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to join this dynamic Award Winning Team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter @teamaccu to find out more about us.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shortlisted applicants will be offered interview arrangements shortly after applying within a time frame that works for you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Helen Hewitt, Matron, on helen.hewitt@bartshealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
